   pollen grains, which have a pebbled surface with triradiate sutures,
   were found on the insect visitors. Fruiting was reduced to 70\% in
   flowers that were covered, while 90\% of the uncovered flowers produced
   fruit. T. alpestre is not agamospermous since flowers lacking stigmas
